      "writtenOn": "2020-06-30T00:50:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t think device_os_type matters.\nuserdebug is default, but on non-Google devices we are not able to use it, so it\u0027s \"user\" there.\nI can\u0027t imagine that we would have different types for the same device.\n\ndevice_os is important, though, since it\u0027s the only indication of the driver version on Android devices (which we have in \"gpu\" for other OSes).",
      "parentUuid": "0ee77eab_49ecb63a",
      "range": {
